{"version": 2, "type": "bm25_book_index", "k1": 1.5, "b": 0.75, "chunks": [{"chunk_id": 0, "source": "samples/sample_code.py", "title": "sample_code", "location": "document, part 1, word 1", "text": "def greet(name: str) -> str: \"\"\"Return a friendly greeting for the supplied name.\"\"\" return f\"Hello, {name}!\" def add(left: float, right: float) -> float: \"\"\"Return the sum of two numbers.\"\"\" return left + right", "word_count": 33, "domain": "programming", "kind": "py"}, {"chunk_id": 1, "source": "samples/sample_law.txt", "title": "sample_law", "location": "document, part 1, word 1", "text": "CONTRACT LAW STUDY NOTES These notes are educational and do not provide legal advice. A contract generally requires an offer, acceptance, consideration, and an intention to create legal relations. Rules and exceptions depend on the jurisdiction and current statute and case law. A court may also consider capacity, legality, certainty of terms, and whether consent was genuine. Always verify legal questions against the applicable legislation, judgments, and a qualified legal professional.", "word_count": 71, "domain": "law", "kind": "txt"}, {"chunk_id": 2, "source": "samples/sample_novel.txt", "title": "sample_novel", "location": "document, part 1, word 1", "text": "THE CLOCKWORK STAR Mira reached the ruined observatory before sunrise. She had come because her brother Arun vanished there three nights earlier, leaving only a note that mentioned a clockwork star beneath the western dome. The townspeople feared the hill and would not follow her. At the broken gate, Mira met Tomas, a young mapmaker carrying a silver compass. The needle did not point north. It turned toward the observatory and trembled whenever the wind crossed the empty windows. Tomas said Arun had borrowed one of his maps and marked a chamber that did not exist on any official plan.", "word_count": 100, "domain": "fiction", "kind": "txt"}, {"chunk_id": 3, "source": "samples/sample_novel.txt", "title": "sample_novel", "location": "document, part 2, word 1", "text": "Inside, they found a brass bell hanging above a staircase. When the bell rang by itself, the staircase rotated and revealed a hidden room. Arun was alive inside the chamber, trapped beside a machine shaped like a star. He explained that the machine copied the night sky and could predict storms, but its gears had locked around his coat. Mira stopped the machine by removing the smallest blue gear. Tomas freed Arun, and the false stars above them faded. They returned to town carrying the blue gear, the silver compass, and Arun's unfinished map.", "word_count": 94, "domain": "fiction", "kind": "txt"}, {"chunk_id": 4, "source": "samples/sample_school.txt", "title": "sample_school", "location": "document, part 1, word 1", "text": "INTRODUCTION TO PHOTOSYNTHESIS Learning objective: explain how plants convert light energy into chemical energy. Photosynthesis occurs mainly in chloroplasts. Chlorophyll absorbs light. During the light-dependent reactions, water contributes electrons and oxygen is released. The Calvin cycle uses carbon dioxide to build sugars. The simplified formula is carbon dioxide plus water plus light energy producing glucose and oxygen. Exercise: Why is chlorophyll important? Answer: chlorophyll absorbs the light energy that begins the process.", "word_count": 72, "domain": "school", "kind": "txt"}], "term_frequencies": [{"def": 2, "greet": 1, "name": 3, "str": 2, "return": 4, "a": 1, "friendly": 1, "greeting": 1, "for": 1, "the": 2, "supplied": 1, "f": 1, "hello": 1, "add": 1, "left": 2, "float": 3, "right": 2, "sum": 1, "of": 1, "two": 1, "numbers": 1}, {"contract": 2, "law": 2, "study": 1, "notes": 2, "these": 1, "are": 1, "educational": 1, "and": 7, "do": 1, "not": 1, "provide": 1, "legal": 4, "advice": 1, "a": 3, "generally": 1, "requires": 1, "an": 2, "offer": 1, "acceptance": 1, "consideration": 1, "intention": 1, "to": 1, "create": 1, "relations": 1, "rules": 1, "exceptions": 1, "depend": 